node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by VisitScotland on September 18, 2021 tagging @oacampey. May be an image of outdoors, monument and castle.

node.text:
Who’s up for a wee taster of the charming capital of Edinburgh?! 🙋‍♀️✨

It wouldn’t be a trip to Edinburgh without a visit to the iconic @edinburghcastle, perched up on Castle Rock overlooking the city 🏰💙 Venture into Edinburgh's Old Town to admire @edinburghuniversity’s New College, which houses the historic & renowned School of Divinity ✨ Fancy getting away from the hustle & bustle of the city centre? Be sure to check out the quiet & peaceful @drneilsgarden, a wee hidden treasure! 🌿 Tickle your tastebuds with a slice (or two!) of pizza from @civerinos_slice & enjoy a wander around @scottishnationalportrait with its ornate interiors and impressive collection of portraits 🖼 Venture out of the city centre towards Leith to discover the variety of street food on offer at @thepittmarket 🍔 To bring your visit to a suitable close, explore the beautiful gardens & glasshouses of @rbgedinburgh 🍃

Where is first on your list of places to visit in Edinburgh? 📝

📷 Edinburgh Castle: @oacampey
📷 School of Divinity: @littlebitofyorkshire
📷 Dr Neil’s Garden: @nehirg05
📷 Civerinos: @alittlebitofclaire
📷 Scottish National Portrait Gallery: @jie_shion
📷 The Pitt: @thepittmarket
📷 Royal Botanic Gardens: @gisforgeorgina

 #VisitScotland #Scotland #Edinburgh #ThisIsEdinburgh #ForeverEdinburgh
